        <h2>Pricing and stack economics for Reviews and UGC in the stack</h2>
        <p>Model total cost: capture + lifecycle + SMS + reviews + loyalty + operator hours. A $400/mo stack that lifts incremental margin $8k/mo beats a $150/mo stack that creates collision cleanup work. Reviews and UGC in the stack decisions should survive a finance review, not only a marketing demo.</p>
        <p>Sequenzy pay-per-email economics reward targeted sends — wide lists with narrow engagement stop taxing you for profiles that never receive lifecycle email. Pair with specialists rather than mega-suite too early unless consolidation truly reduces weekly operator minutes.</p>
